  "text": "The prometheus/prometheus repository enforces TLS and authentication for remote write endpoints through multiple layers of validation and configuration:\n\n## Configuration and Validation Layer (config/config.go)\n\nThe RemoteWriteConfig struct (lines 1418-1440) includes an HTTPClientConfig field that inherits TLS and authentication settings from prometheus/common. The configuration parsing happens in the UnmarshalYAML method (lines 1448-1478) which:\n\n1. Calls HTTPClientConfig.Validate() to validate TLS certificate and key files exist and are properly paired\n2. Calls validateAuthConfigs() to ensure at most one authentication method is configured among: basic_auth, authorization, oauth2, sigv4, azuread, and google_iam\n3. Calls validateHeaders() to prevent manual configuration of the Authorization header\n\nThe validateAuthConfigs function (lines 1491-1515) specifically enforces mutual exclusivity between different authentication methods. The validateHeaders function (lines 1529-1539) validates that the Authorization header is not set manually in custom headers, ensuring all authorization is configured through the proper configuration parameters.\n\n## Client Creation Layer (storage/remote/client.go)\n\nThe ClientConfig struct (lines 128-141) contains the HTTPClientConfig field. When creating clients, NewWriteClient (lines 183-238) and NewReadClient (lines 151-180) call config_util.NewClientFromConfig() with the HTTPClientConfig, which validates and applies TLS settings. These functions also handle special authentication mechanisms:\n\n- Bearer token authentication (via HTTPClientConfig.BearerToken and BearerTokenFile)\n- Basic authentication (via HTTPClientConfig.BasicAuth with Username and Password)\n- OAuth2 (via HTTPClientConfig.OAuth2)\n- SigV4 authentication (applied via sigv4.NewSigV4RoundTripper at line 199)\n- Azure AD authentication (applied via azuread.NewAzureADRoundTripper at lines 206-209)\n- Google IAM authentication (applied via googleiam.NewRoundTripper at lines 213-216)\n\n## Remote Write Configuration Application (storage/remote/write.go)\n\nThe WriteStorage.ApplyConfig method (lines 139-236) applies remote write configurations to the storage system. For each RemoteWriteConfig, it creates a ClientConfig (lines 169-180) containing the HTTPClientConfig, SigV4Config, AzureADConfig, and GoogleIAMConfig, then passes this to NewWriteClient which validates and creates the HTTP client with proper TLS and authentication setup.\n\n## Tooling Validation (cmd/promtool/main.go)\n\nThe checkTLSConfig function (lines 790-810) validates TLS configurations by:\n- Ensuring cert files are paired with key files (lines 791-796)\n- Checking that certificate and key files exist and are accessible when not in syntax-only mode (lines 802-809)\n\nThe checkConfig function (lines 663-788) validates scrape configurations for TLS and Authorization settings (lines 703-711).\n\n## Azure AD and Google IAM Integration\n\nThe storage/remote/azuread/azuread.go file provides Azure AD token authentication through NewAzureADRoundTripper, which wraps HTTP requests with Azure AD bearer tokens. The storage/remote/googleiam/googleiam.go file provides Google Cloud IAM authentication through NewRoundTripper, which adds Google Cloud credentials to requests.\n\nTogether, these components enforce comprehensive TLS and authentication compliance for all remote write endpoints in Prometheus."
}

